The paper is about image captioning, which is a task related to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The proposed model involves the use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) and fusion of multiple encoders, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments are conducted on the MSCOCO dataset, which is a popular benchmark for multimedia tasks (cs.MM).
